feat(visualizer): mad scientist mode — 5x slider range, editable values, overdrive metrics

Three changes to let users push the visualizers way beyond their
default safe range:

- Default playback volume lowered from 100% to 40% for new users
  (anyone with an existing localStorage value keeps their setting).
- Visualizer slider maxes multiplied by 5 (Gain 2.5→12.5, Bass/Mid/
  High 2→10, Bloom 2.5→12.5, Speed 2.5→12.5). Minimums unchanged.
- Double-click any control value (the number shown above each slider)
  to edit it as a free-form number with no clamp; Enter commits,
  Escape cancels. Values outside the slider range display in the bass
  accent color and the slider thumb pins at its nearest edge. Touching
  the slider after typing an out-of-range value snaps the value back
  inside the range, which is the expected explicit-interaction behavior.
- AudioMetricsProvider's per-frame clamp on bass/mid/high/energy/beat
  raised from 0..1 to 0..10. Previously the cap was hit at moderate
  volume with the old slider maxes, which meant raising any of those
  sliders past their old top did nothing — overdrive sliders now
  actually overdrive. 10x headroom is enough for genuinely wild visuals
  without risking NaN/Infinity propagation in shaders.
